<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-64-0762 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author discusses the dangers of human error and how it can cause anuclear war. Drug and alcohol abuse is a persistent problem in the armedforces. Paranoid disorder can also cause people to act in a manner thatthey normally wouldn't consider. In a moment of extreme internationaltension, the act of an insane person or group could set off a nuclearwar. Group thinking is also dangerous because isolated groups are oftenmore reckless in their decisions than individuals.</TEXT></DOC>